---
import Analytics from "@vercel/analytics/astro";
import { Image } from "astro:assets";
import pozoolLogo from "../assets/pozool-logo.png";

const lastUpdated = "April 29, 2026";
---

<html lang="en">
  <head>
    <meta charset="utf-8" />
    <link rel="icon" href="/favicon.ico" />
    <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1" />
    <meta name="description" content="Pozool terms of service for customers and users." />
    <title>Terms of Service | Pozool</title>
    <style>
      :root {
        --background: oklch(99% 0.005 70);
        --foreground: #000;
        --card: oklch(100% 0 0);
        --primary: oklch(70% 0.19 45);
        --muted-foreground: #000;
        --border: oklch(92% 0.012 70);
        --surface-warm: oklch(97% 0.02 70);
      }

      * {
        box-sizing: border-box;
      }

      body {
        margin: 0;
        font-family: Inter, system-ui, sans-serif;
        background: var(--background);
        color: var(--foreground);
        line-height: 1.7;
      }

      a {
        color: inherit;
      }

      .container {
        width: min(100%, 56rem);
        margin: 0 auto;
        padding: 0 1.5rem;
      }

      header,
      footer {
        background: var(--surface-warm);
        border-bottom: 1px solid var(--border);
      }

      footer {
        border-top: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-bottom: 0;
      }

      .nav,
      footer .container {
        display: flex;
        align-items: center;
        justify-content: space-between;
        gap: 1rem;
        min-height: 4rem;
      }

      .brand {
        display: inline-flex;
        align-items: center;
        gap: 0.625rem;
        font-weight: 700;
        text-decoration: none;
      }

      .brand img {
        width: 2.25rem;
        height: 2.25rem;
        border-radius: 0.625rem;
      }

      .nav-links {
        display: flex;
        gap: 1rem;
        color: var(--muted-foreground);
        font-size: 0.9rem;
      }

      main {
        padding: 5rem 0;
      }

      .panel {
        padding: clamp(1.5rem, 4vw, 3rem);
        border: 1px solid var(--border);
        border-radius: 1.25rem;
        background: var(--card);
      }

      h1 {
        margin: 0;
        font-size: clamp(2.5rem, 6vw, 4rem);
        line-height: 1;
        letter-spacing: -0.04em;
      }

      h2 {
        margin: 2.5rem 0 0.75rem;
        font-size: 1.25rem;
        line-height: 1.25;
      }

      p,
      li {
        color: var(--muted-foreground);
      }

      .updated {
        margin-top: 1rem;
        color: var(--primary);
        font-weight: 700;
      }

      ul {
        padding-left: 1.25rem;
      }
    </style>
  </head>
  <body>
    <header>
      <div class="container nav">
        <a class="brand" href="/">
          <Image src={pozoolLogo} alt="Pozool" width={64} height={64} format="webp" />
          <span>Pozool</span>
        </a>
        <nav class="nav-links" aria-label="Legal navigation">
          <a href="/privacy">Privacy</a>
          <a href="/">Home</a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </header>

    <main>
      <div class="container">
        <article class="panel">
          <h1>Terms of Service</h1>
          <p class="updated">Last updated: {lastUpdated}</p>

          <p>
            These Terms of Service ("Terms") govern access to and use of Pozool websites, products,
            applications, tools, and related services (collectively, the "Service"). By accessing or
            using the Service, creating an account, requesting a demo, or entering into an order,
            statement of work, subscription, or similar agreement with Pozool, you agree to these
            Terms.
          </p>

          <h2>1. The Service</h2>
          <p>
            Pozool provides property management software and related operational tools for rental
            operators, including reservations, calendars, payment tracking, guest communication,
            reporting, and operational workflows. Features may change, be added, or be removed over
            time.
          </p>

          <h2>2. Eligibility and Accounts</h2>
          <p>
            You must have authority to bind the business or organization you represent. You are
            responsible for all activity under your account, including activity by employees,
            contractors, administrators, invited users, and anyone using your credentials. You must
            keep login credentials confidential and promptly notify us of suspected unauthorized
            access.
          </p>

          <h2>3. Customer Responsibilities</h2>
          <p>You are responsible for:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Providing accurate account, billing, property, reservation, guest, and operational information.</li>
            <li>Obtaining rights, permissions, notices, and consents required to use data in Pozool.</li>
            <li>Ensuring your properties, listings, pricing, taxes, fees, rules, messages, and guest-facing content comply with applicable laws and platform rules.</li>
            <li>Managing user permissions, reviewing automated outputs, and verifying operational tasks before relying on them.</li>
            <li>Maintaining appropriate insurance, licenses, permits, tax registrations, and property compliance.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>4. Third-Party Channels and Providers</h2>
          <p>
            The Service may connect with third-party booking channels, payment processors, messaging
            providers, analytics providers, hosting providers, or other tools. Third-party services
            are not controlled by Pozool. We are not responsible for their availability, accuracy,
            security, fees, rules, policy changes, account restrictions, lost reservations, delayed
            messages, payment failures, or other actions or omissions. Your use of third-party
            services is governed by their own terms.
          </p>

          <h2>5. Payments, Fees, and Taxes</h2>
          <p>
            Fees, billing cycles, payment methods, and plan details are set out in the applicable
            order, invoice, written agreement, or product checkout flow. Unless we expressly state
            otherwise in writing, fees are non-refundable and are exclusive of taxes, duties,
            currency conversion costs, bank charges, and third-party fees. You authorize us and our
            payment processors to charge your payment method for amounts due. You are responsible
            for taxes related to your use of the Service and your rental operations.
          </p>

          <h2>6. Late Payment and Suspension</h2>
          <p>
            If payment is late, declined, disputed, reversed, or otherwise not received, we may
            suspend or limit access to the Service, stop work, withhold support, charge late fees or
            collection costs where allowed by law, and terminate the account. Suspension does not
            relieve you of payment obligations.
          </p>

          <h2>7. Acceptable Use</h2>
          <p>You may not:</p>
          <ul>
            <li>Use the Service for illegal, deceptive, abusive, harmful, or discriminatory activity.</li>
            <li>Interfere with, reverse engineer, scrape, overload, or compromise the Service.</li>
            <li>Upload malware, unauthorized personal data, infringing content, or content you do not have rights to use.</li>
            <li>Misrepresent reservations, payments, property availability, guest communications, or operational status.</li>
            <li>Use the Service to violate third-party platform rules or applicable laws.</li>
          </ul>

          <h2>8. Customer Content and Data</h2>
          <p>
            You retain ownership of content and data you submit to the Service. You grant Pozool a
            limited license to host, copy, process, transmit, display, and use that content and data
            as needed to provide, secure, support, and improve the Service, comply with law, and
            enforce these Terms.
          </p>

          <h2>9. Pozool Intellectual Property</h2>
          <p>
            Pozool and its licensors own the Service, software, designs, workflows, documentation,
            branding, and related intellectual property. These Terms do not transfer ownership to
            you. You may use the Service only as permitted by these Terms and any applicable
            agreement.
          </p>

          <h2>10. Beta Features and Product Changes</h2>
          <p>
            We may offer beta, trial, preview, or experimental features. These are provided for
            evaluation, may be changed or discontinued at any time, and may be less reliable than
            generally available features.
          </p>

          <h2>11. Support</h2>
          <p>
            We may provide support through the channels and during the hours we make available. We
            do not guarantee any specific response time or resolution unless expressly agreed in
            writing.
          </p>

          <h2>12. Disclaimers</h2>
          <p>
            The Service is provided "as is" and "as available." To the maximum extent permitted by
            law, Pozool disclaims all warranties, express or implied, including warranties of
            merchantability, fitness for a particular purpose, non-infringement, availability,
            accuracy, and error-free operation. Pozool does not guarantee that the Service will
            prevent losses, increase revenue, ensure legal compliance, avoid double bookings, detect
            every payment issue, or replace professional judgment.
          </p>

          <h2>13. Limitation of Liability</h2>
          <p>
            To the maximum extent permitted by law, Pozool will not be liable for indirect,
            incidental, special, consequential, exemplary, punitive, or lost-profit damages, or for
            loss of data, revenue, goodwill, reservations, platform accounts, or business
            interruption. Pozool’s total liability for all claims relating to the Service will not
            exceed the amount you paid to Pozool for the Service in the three months before the
            event giving rise to the claim, or USD $100 if no amounts were paid.
          </p>

          <h2>14. Indemnification</h2>
          <p>
            You agree to defend, indemnify, and hold harmless Pozool, its owners, team members,
            contractors, and service providers from claims, damages, liabilities, losses, costs, and
            expenses, including reasonable attorneys’ fees, arising from your use of the Service,
            your properties or rental operations, your content or data, your breach of these Terms,
            your violation of law, or disputes with guests, owners, employees, contractors, service
            providers, booking channels, or payment processors.
          </p>

          <h2>15. Termination</h2>
          <p>
            You may stop using the Service at any time, subject to any payment commitments in your
            agreement with us. We may suspend or terminate access if you breach these Terms, fail to
            pay, create risk for Pozool or others, misuse the Service, or if we discontinue the
            Service. Sections intended to survive termination will survive, including payment,
            intellectual property, disclaimers, limitation of liability, indemnification, and
            dispute terms.
          </p>

          <h2>16. Privacy</h2>
          <p>
            Our Privacy Policy explains how we collect and use information. By using the Service,
            you agree to the Privacy Policy.
          </p>

          <h2>17. Governing Law and Disputes</h2>
          <p>
            These Terms are governed by the laws of the State of Florida, United States, without
            regard to conflict-of-law rules, unless another governing law is stated in a written
            agreement signed by Pozool. Courts located in Florida will have exclusive jurisdiction,
            except that Pozool may seek injunctive or equitable relief in any appropriate court.
          </p>

          <h2>18. Changes to These Terms</h2>
          <p>
            We may update these Terms from time to time. Updates are effective when posted unless a
            different date is stated. Continued use of the Service after an update means you accept
            the updated Terms.
          </p>

          <h2>19. Contact</h2>
          <p>
            Questions about these Terms can be sent to hello@pozool.com.
          </p>
        </article>
      </div>
    </main>

    <footer>
      <div class="container">
        <span>© 2026 Pozool</span>
        <a href="/privacy">Privacy Policy</a>
      </div>
    </footer>
    <Analytics />
  </body>
</html>
